    {
      "id": "/page/0/TextInlineMath/7",
      "block_type": "TextInlineMath",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"TextInlineMath\">The long position in a variance swap receives <i>N</i> dollars for every point by which the stock's realized variance <i>σ</i><sup>R</sup> <sup>2</sup> has exceeded the inception fair value <i>K</i>var. See [6] for one of the earliest, but most comprehensive, references on variance swaps. In this reference, the authors discuss replication problems due to strike spacing and gapping of the underlying, for example.</p>",
      "page": 489,
      "polygon": [
