    {
      "id": "/page/0/Text/12",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">Uses of variance swaps include trading the level of volatility (variance swaps are a more pure way to do this compared to straddles), trading the realized/ implied vol spread, hedging of volatility exposures, or trading volatility on a forward basis via forward variance swaps. See [1] for more details about variance swaps, market practices, and their use in vol spread trading and correlation trading.</p>",
