    {
      "id": "/page/1/Text/17",
      "block_type": "Text",
      "html": "<p block-type=\"Text\">In [5], the authors derive general results on market risk for variance swaps. Because variance is additive, a variance swap partway through its life is valued partly by realized vol (already observed) and partly by unrealized/implied vol, which is yet to be observed.</p>",
      "page": 128,
      "polygon": [
        [
          304.9609375,
          92.93836978131213
        ],
        [
          517.0632911392405,
